      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">53.243</ph> Contract modifications (SF 30).</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <p class="- topic/p " id="d3859e8">
            <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">
               <xref href="https://www.gsa.gov/forms-library/amendment-solicitationmodification-contract"
                     format="html"
                     scope="external"
                     class="- topic/xref "> SF 30</xref> (Rev.11/2016), Amendment of Solicitation/ Modification of Contract.</i>
            <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref href="https://www.gsa.gov/forms-library/amendment-solicitationmodification-contract"
                     format="html"
                     scope="external"
                     class="- topic/xref ">SF 30</xref>
            </ph>is prescribed for use in amending invitation for bids, as specified in <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref href="14.208.dita#FAR_14_208"
                     base="i1110854"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">14.208</xref>
            </ph>; modifying purchase and delivery orders, as specified in <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref href="13.302-3.dita#FAR_13_302_3"
                     base="i1111519"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">13.302-3</xref>
            </ph>; and modifying contracts, as specified in <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref href="42.1203.dita#FAR_42_1203"
                     base="i1074602"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">42.1203</xref>(h)</ph>, <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref href="43.301.dita#FAR_43_301"
                     base="i1073804"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">43.301</xref>
            </ph>, <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref href="49.602-5.dita#FAR_49_602_5"
                     base="i1067374"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">49.602-5</xref>
            </ph>, and elsewhere in this regulation. The form may also be used to amend solicitations for negotiated contracts, as specified in <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref href="15.210.dita#FAR_15_210"
                     base="i1109167"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">15.210</xref>
            </ph>(b). Pending the publication of a new edition of the form, Instruction (b), Item 3 (effective date), is revised in paragraphs (3) and (5) as follows:</p>
         <p outputclass="NoIndent" class="- topic/p ">(b) Item3 (effective date).</p>
         <p class="- topic/p "/>
         <p outputclass="NoIndent" class="- topic/p ">(3) For a modification issued as a confirming notice of termination for the convenience of the Government, the effective date of the confirming notice shall be the same as the effective date of the initial notice.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p "/>
         <p outputclass="NoIndent" class="- topic/p ">(5) For a modification confirming the termination contracting officer’s previous letter determination of the amount due in settlement of a contract termination for convenience, the effective date shall be the same as the effective date of the previous letter determination.</p>
      </conbody>
